dependencies.name: py-setuptools
dependencies.description:
A Python utility that aids in the process of downloading, building,
upgrading, installing, and uninstalling Python packages.

dependent_to.name: py-ray
dependent_to.description:
A system for parallel and distributed Python that unifies the ML
ecosystem.

dependent_to.name: py-zarr
dependent_to.description:
Zarr is a Python package providing an implementation of chunked,
compressed, N-dimensional arrays.

dependent_to.name: py-mmtf-python
dependent_to.description:
The macromolecular transmission format (MMTF) is a binary encoding of
biological structures.

dependent_to.name: py-msgpack-numpy
dependent_to.description:
This package provides encoding and decoding routines that enable the
serialization and deserialization of numerical and array data types
provided by numpy using the highly efficient msgpack format.
Serialization of Python's native complex data types is also supported.

dependent_to.name: py-numcodecs
dependent_to.description:
Numcodecs is a Python package providing buffer compression and
transformation codecs for use in data storage and communication
applications.

dependent_to.name: py-python-box
dependent_to.description:
Advanced Python dictionaries with dot notation access Box will
automatically make otherwise inaccessible keys safe to access as an
attribute. You can always pass conversion_box=False to Box to disable
that behavior. Also, all new dict and lists added to a Box or BoxList
object are converted automatically.
